triageapp.database

Class TriageDBAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • triageapp.database.DBAdapter
      • triageapp.database.TriageDBAdapter

  • public class TriageDBAdapter
extends DBAdapter
    Triage database access helper class. Extends DBAdapter to inherit the ability to open/create/close the database. Defines the basic CRUD operations for the Triage+ app. Gives the ability to list all information for a specific Patient or ERVisit, create new rows in the tables corresponding to a new ERVisit, VitalSigns, Prescription, or Patient. Also allows retrieval and modification of a specific ERVisit. Uses Cursors.

      • createERVisit

        public long createERVisit(long arrivalTime,
                 String patientHealthCard,
                 int urgency)
        Create a new ERVisit row in the ERVisit table. If successfully created return the new rowId for that ERVisit, otherwise return -1 to indicate failure.
        Parameters:
        arrivalTime - The arrival time at the ER.
        patientHealthCard - The patient who is visiting the ER.
        urgency - The urgency value of the visit.
        Returns:
        rowId or -1 if failed.

      • createVitalSigns

        public boolean createVitalSigns(long ervisitID,
                       int sys,
                       int dia,
                       float temp,
                       float HR,
                       long timeStamp,
                       int urgency)
        Create a new VitalSigns row in the VitalSigns table, and update the urgency value of the ERVisit during which this set of vital signs was recorded. If successfully created return true.
        Parameters:
        ervisitID - The row id of the visit in the ERVisit table. that the vital signs are for.
        sys - Systolic blood pressure value.
        dia - Diastolic blood pressure value.
        HR - Heart Rate value.
        timeStamp - The time these vital signs were taken.
        urgency - The updated urgency value of the visit based on the new vital sign values.
        Returns:
        true if insertion and update are successful.

        Parameters:

        name - The name of the medication.
        instructions - The medication instructions.
        Returns:
        true if insertion is successful.

      • updateERVisit

        public boolean updateERVisit(long ervisitID,
                    long timeSeenByDoctor)
        Overloading method. Update the ERVisit using the details provided. The ERVisit to be updated is specified using the rowId, and it is altered to use the time seen by doctor value passed in.
        Parameters:
        ervisitID - id of the ER visit to update.
        timeSeenByDoctor - Value to set the ERVisit's TIMESEENBYDOCTOR column to.
        Returns:
        true if the ER Visit was successfully updated, false otherwise.

      • updateERVisit

        public boolean updateERVisit(long ervisitID,
                    boolean closed)
        Overloading method. Update the ERVisit using the details provided. The ERVisit to be updated is specified using the rowId, and it is altered to use the closed value passed in.
        Parameters:
        ervisitID - id of the ER visit to update.
        closed - Value to set the ERVisit's CLOSED column to.
        Returns:
        true if the ER Visit was successfully updated, false otherwise.
